(''biochemistry'') relating to [[structural biology]], which describes the general [[three-dimensional]] form of local regions of [[biopolymer]]s, such as [[protein]]s, [[DNA]], and [[RNA]]. It does not, however, refer to specific positions in [[three-dimensional]] space, which are considered to be [[tertiary structure]]. The secondary structure of a protein may include regions of [[alpha helix]], [[3_10 helix]], [[pi helix]], [[beta sheet]], [[beta turn]], [[omega loop]], and [[random coil]].